WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.500
We believe technology can empower everyone to achieve more.

00:00:06.500 --> 00:00:16.000
A man uses a wheelchair equipped with a computer.
Many people are nonverbal but still have much to say.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:24.000
I want the exact same information
that my hearing friends have.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Barriers to communication exist everywhere,
but it is time to see barriers as opportunities.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
Soundscape

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:46.000
A person wearing headphones uses a guide dog.
Soundscape technology helps build a mental map
of the environment through audio cues.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.000
Eye Control

00:00:48.000 --> 00:01:01.000
A man living with ALS uses eye-tracking technology
to control a computer.
While ALS can limit movement, technology can restore
communication and independence.

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:03.000
SwiftKey Symbols

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:16.000
A tablet displays symbols that help children communicate.
There is no better feeling than hearing a child express
something they have always wanted to say.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:18.000
Learning Tools

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:31.000
A student uses reading tools that adjust text spacing and layout.
Seeing more space between words helps with focus
and comprehension.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:33.000
Microsoft Translator

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:50.000
A smartphone translates spoken language in real time.
Being able to see what is said has been a huge help.
The system improves over time and helps students receive
information in their preferred language.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:57.000
Communication is essential for connection and belonging.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.000
Assistive Communication for Autism

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:12.000
An application converts spoken phrases into pictograms
and spoken output.
This helps a child communicate more spontaneously
and build relationships.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:14.000
Seeing AI

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:27.000
A blind couple describes raising their young child.
The Seeing AI app helps them interpret the visual world,
including their child's school environment.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:37.000
Artificial intelligence is already improving accessibility,
but there is still much more to be done.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:42.500
We're just getting started.
Let's see what you can do.

00:02:42.500 --> 00:02:44.871
AI for Accessibility - Microsoft
